I purposely didnâ€™t translate miyakoochi in the lyrics. Miyakoochi is a very waï¼ˆå’Œï¼‰word or traditional japanesy word. It is to return home after losing hopes and dreams in the city/capital. Miyako, meaning large city or in this case Tokyo, and ochi, meaning falling. A lot of japanese people often jyoukyou ï¼ˆä¸Šäº¬ï¼‰meaning moving to the capital. It is often associated with finding dreams and achieving them in the capital. Miyakoochi can be thought of as the opposite. After finding out that there is no hope for them, people Miyakoochi, going back to their home town or countryside. Interpretation is probably up to the listener, but it could be like escaping, leaving or giving up on their current lives. Possibly even breaking up and falling out of love. What works well in the song is metaphorically contrasting it to tides. Similarly they go back into the ocean after reaching the shore and that is likely the message of this song.

There is also a lot of 'puns' in these lyrics. For example 'ã•ã‚ˆã†ãªã‚‰â€™ and 'å·¦æ§˜ãªã‚‰' goodbye and 'if it is that' and alot more others. These nuances are used very often in Yorushika songs so it is cool to see the word play affect the lyrics so much. 

I am a Japanese high school student living in Australia and I tried translating lyrics for the first time! Of course I started with a Yorushika with their unique and a little ambiguous lyrics. I really hope this helps people connect with the beautiful song more easily. Of course this has my perspective on it, but I feel confident I did better than google translate.

* Literally, the songâ€™s title means â€œcapital [city] falling/conclusionâ€; itâ€™s a very traditional word used to describe a person leaving an important, high-culture Japanese city (usually Kyoto or Tokyo, depending on which was the capital at a given time period). Sometimes it refers to just moving away, other times literal exile, but thereâ€™s typically a slight connotation of shame or loss.

** The word æµ·çŒ« (umineko) literally means â€œsea catâ€, but refers to the bird known in English as the black-tailed gull (apparently because their calls sound like meowing and/or their long tails appear catlike). I thought that the literal translation suited the tone and imagescape of the lyrics much better, especially since the next line specifies that they are, in fact, birds.

*** The â€œè½ã¡â€ (ochi) in â€œdropping and flowingâ€ is the same as the one in the title (éƒ½è½ã¡ / miyako ochi), hence why theyâ€™re translated with the same English word. At the end of the line, æ†‚ã (uki) is a fairly archaic word meaning anguish, sorrow, or difficulty; however, it sounds the same as æµ®ã, meaning floating or buoyancy, continuing the lineâ€™s thing-falling-in-water metaphor (eg, â€œdropping and flowing in the water, it eventually floatsâ€). The word â€œpiqueâ€ was my attempt at reconciling these two opposing meaningsâ€” thereâ€™s an old, obscure definition of â€œto piqueâ€ meaning to be resentful or perturbed, and itâ€™s homophonous with â€œto peakâ€, or reach the highest point of something, which in water would be floating.

Even if you give people the most corporate to the point livestream ever nothing of value was said and the vague statements about brand direction are in fact further causes for concern. 

Idk what direction they're trying to go. I think it's dumb to blame vtubers for being vtubers but I certainly don't think they have the experience to run a v branch just because they're a big name in the fictional idol world. I don't think this is the big shift they're making but whatever shift they're making sounds like something that's setting a bunch of stuff on fire, at least for sidem. If they start torching other branches too that's even more concerning, but if they singled out sidem as a sacrificial lamb despite being in the top 5 rhythm games and top 3 joseimuke games that's already unforgivable without anything to replace it and they know it . I'm deeply worried about im@s management rn, as I'd imagine we all are. They're trying to pass sidem off as a flop despite everyone sticking around no matter what they do and they were the ones that always gave us the short end of the stock in the first place.

Sidem has a unique appeal and something very special to us that makes us stick around, even for a lot of people who like other im@s properties too it stands out in its own way. We never deserved this and profit is clearly not the cause if it's taking in cash even through mismanagement and mess.

MOIW is beginning to feel like the end of the good days rather than the beginning of a new unified tradition, and as a sidem fan, a long-term im@s fan since I was a kid, and as someone who's never been able to make it to in person events and has to wait til I'm able to due to health and money concerns, this is deeply disappointing. I don't want another fandom I'm in to have the rug pulled before I can engage with it in every way I wanted to. It's too cruel.

This is actually SO dissapointing and depressing. This game hasn't been lasted this long yet you're shutting it down. I also hate the fact that this is the only; game that keeps sideM alive, so sad :(
